This paper discusses frequent itemset mining, which is a common data mining technique used in various fields such as database systems (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper focuses on comparing the performance of three frequent itemset mining algorithms, which is a topic that falls under these sub-categories.
